## Summary

Fixes #92061. Two related fixes for `textScore: 0` in hybrid memory search:

### Fix 1: CJK tokens bypass FTS5 MATCH path

In `planKeywordSearch`, CJK tokens with 3+ characters were sent to `matchTerms` as quoted phrase matches (`MATCH "飞书插件配置"`), which rarely match with the trigram tokenizer. All CJK tokens now go to `substringTerms` for LIKE matching.

```typescript
// Before
if (SHORT_CJK_TRIGRAM_RE.test(token) && Array.from(token).length < 3) {
    substringTerms.push(token);
    continue;
}
matchTerms.push(token); // Long CJK → quoted phrase MATCH (fails)

// After
if (SHORT_CJK_TRIGRAM_RE.test(token)) {
    substringTerms.push(token); // All CJK → LIKE matching
    continue;
}
```

### Fix 2: No LIKE fallback when MATCH returns 0 rows

The LIKE fallback only triggered when FTS5 MATCH threw an exception. When MATCH returned 0 rows (common with strict AND queries), no fallback ran. Now a LIKE fallback with OR-based matching triggers on empty MATCH results.

```typescript
// Added after MATCH succeeds but returns 0 rows
if (rows.length === 0) {
    const allTerms = uniqueStrings([...queryTokens, ...plan.substringTerms]);
    const fbLike = allTerms.map(() => " OR text LIKE ? ESCAPE '\\'").join("");
    // ... OR-based LIKE fallback
}
```

## Verification

| Query | Before | After |
|-------|--------|-------|
| `飞书插件配置` (CJK) | textScore=0, MATCH fails | textScore>0, LIKE fallback works |
| `cron delivery announce` (EN) | textScore=0, no fallback | textScore=1, LIKE fallback works |
| `dreaming consolidation` (EN) | textScore=0.89 | textScore=0.89 (unchanged) |

